race.comment: PRINCE TYCOON (6) clearly on top. He was a very promising 2yo having won in fast time on debut and resumed at Moonee Valley in the G3 Red Anchor Stakes, starting second-elect when setting a very strong speed in front. He was beaten five lengths there but the winner was dominant and he was close up behind the others. Fitter now and back in grade, he should take a power of catching. DOLLAR CHASER (3) has been good in two runs back, trying hard behind a progressive mare at Sale second up. He doesn't win out of turn but looks a strong each-way chance at odds. BARBARIC LAD (8) is knocking on the door having just found one better his past two. Tricky draw but he'll be rattling home. EXPRESS GUARD (9) presents third up off two solid runs this time in. He is off a let-up here but did basically cross the line with subsequent Victoria Derby winner Observer last time at Sandown which reads very well. UNTAPPED (7) resumes with pieces of form that go well in this.
